        <br>
        <h1 class="text-center">CPR</h1>
        <br>
            

        <div>

            <div class="card text-light bg-secondary">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Scene survey/environment check</h5>
                    <ul class="card-text">
                        <li>No fire</li>
                        <li>No wire</li>
                        <li>No gas</li>
                        <li>No glass</li>
                    <ul/>
                </div>
            </div>


            <div class="card text-light bg-secondary">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Check responsiveness</h5>
                    <ul class="card-text">
                        <li>Talk to them "can you hear me?"</li>
                        <li>Tap the ground around their ear</li>
                        <li>Pinch their ear</li>
                    </ul>
                    <img src="https://www.healthywa.wa.gov.au/~/media/Images/HealthyWA/Articles/First-aid/1-sja-response.jpg" alt="Responsiveness">
                </div>
            </div>


            <div class="card text-light bg-secondary">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Tell bystander to call EMS & get an AED</h5>
                    <img src="https://cerid.uw.edu/sites/cerid.uw.edu/files/styles/page_embedded_image/public/uploads/Automated_external_defibrillator.jpg?itok=KagiC7PP" alt="AED">
                </div>
            </div>


            <div class="card text-light bg-secondary">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Check breathing</h5>
                    <ul class="card-text">
                        <li>Tilt their head & lift their chin to open airway</li>
                        <li>Look towards abdomen, check for movement (breathing)</li>
                        <li>Listen for breathing</li>
                        <li>Feel under nose for breathing</li>
                        <li>If victim is breathing, do not perform CPR. See <a href="/treatment/unconsciousness" target="_blank" class="link-info">unconsciousness</a></li>
                    </ul>
                    <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/originals/ca/47/1e/ca471e64cad9a16c76d723f76bb09262.jpg" alt="Head tilt, chin lift">
                </div>
            </div>


            <div class="card text-light bg-secondary">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Perform 30 chest compressions to 2 rescue breaths</h5>
                    <ul class="card-text">
                        
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card text-light bg-secondary">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Chest compressions</h5>
                    <ul class="card-text">
                        <li>Location: between the nipple line, or 1 handprint below armpit line</li>
                        <li>Adult: one hand over the other</li>
                        <li>Child: one hand</li>
                        <li>Infant: 2 fingers</li>
                        <li>Don't bend elbows</li>
                        <li>Look for chest recoil (comes back up)</li>
                        <li>2in/5cm deep for adult</li>
                        <li>1/3 of chest for infant/child</li>
                    </ul>
                    <img src="https://www.emssafetyservices.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/CPR_web_DSC_0083.jpg" alt="Chest compressions">
                </div>
            </div>


            <div class="card text-light bg-secondary">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Rescue breaths</h5>
                    <ul class="card-text">
                        <li>Adult/child: normal breath (not a deep breath)</li>
                        <li>Infant: smaller breath (fill your cheeks)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <img src="https://www.emssafetyservices.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/rescue-breaths.jpg" alt="Rescue breaths">
                </div>
            </div>


            <div class="card text-light bg-secondary">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">AED</h5>
                    <ul class="card-text">
                        <li>Take off/cut victim's shirt</li>
                        <li>If chest is wet, dry off with towel</li>
                        <li>Ensure ground is dry</li>
                        <li>Follow AED prompts</li>
                    </ul>
                    <img src="https://invention.si.edu/sites/default/files/styles/story_banner_image/public/blog_bedi-joyce-2016-02-24_aed-trainingsample-banner-edit.jpg?itok=fQ-Tf0e3" alt="AED">
                </div>
            </div>


            <div class="card text-light bg-secondary">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">When to stop</h5>
                    <ul class="card-text">
                        <li>When EMS arrives</li>
                        <li>When you are too tired to continue CPR</li>
                        <li>When you are in danger</li>
                        <li>When the victim vomits, becomes conscious, or starts breathing</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

